# Example .envrc file for direnv + Nix integration
#
# Copy this file to your project root as `.envrc` and customize as needed.
# direnv will automatically load the Nix environment when you enter the directory.
#
# Usage:
#   1. Copy this file: cp ~/.dotfiles/.envrc.example .envrc
#   2. Allow direnv: direnv allow
#   3. The Nix environment will auto-load on cd into this directory

# ============================================================================
# Option 1: Use Nix Flakes (Recommended)
# ============================================================================
# Loads the development shell from the flake in the dotfiles repo
# Replace the path with your actual dotfiles location

use flake ~/dotfiles/nix

# ============================================================================
# Option 2: Use Nix Flakes from Current Directory
# ============================================================================
# If your project has its own flake.nix in the root:

# use flake

# ============================================================================
# Option 3: Load Specific Nix Packages
# ============================================================================
# Load specific packages without a flake:

# use nix --packages nodejs python3 go

# ============================================================================
# Option 4: Use Shell.nix (Traditional Nix)
# ============================================================================
# If you have a shell.nix in your project:

# use nix

# ============================================================================
# Additional Configuration
# ============================================================================

# Set custom environment variables
# export PROJECT_NAME="my-project"
# export API_KEY="your-api-key"

# Add local bin to PATH
# PATH_add ./bin

# Load .env file if it exists
# dotenv_if_exists

# Watch additional files for changes
# watch_file package.json
# watch_file Cargo.toml

# ============================================================================
# Mise/RTX Integration
# ============================================================================
# If you're using mise for version management:

# use mise

# Or for specific mise profile:
# use mise --profile production

# ============================================================================
# Language-Specific Examples
# ============================================================================

# Python with virtualenv
# layout python python3.11
# export VIRTUAL_ENV=.venv

# Node.js with specific version
# use node 20

# Ruby
# use ruby 3.2.0

# ============================================================================
# Notes
# ============================================================================
#
# - direnv will reload when .envrc or watched files change
# - Always review .envrc before running `direnv allow` for security
# - Add .envrc to .gitignore (it's project-specific)
# - Add .envrc.example to git for team consistency
# - Use `direnv reload` to force reload after manual changes
